    "37421281": {
      "title": "Novel metabolic pathway of estrone and 17β-estradiol catalyzed by cytochrome P-450",
      "abstract": "We have already reported that the quinol formation from some para -alkylphenols, which is a novel metabolic pathway catalyzed by cytochrome P-450, occurs in a rat liver microsomal system (Ohe et al., 1997). In the present study, we investigated whether estrone and 17β-estadiol, each of which contains a p -alkylphenol moiety, are also oxidized into the corresponding quinols by cytochrome P-450. Six recombinant human cytochrome P-450 enzymes, CYP1A1, CYP1A2, CYP2B6, CYP2C9, CYP2E1, and CYP3A4, were tested. The results show that estrone and 17β-estadiol were converted into the corresponding quinols by CYP1A1, CYP2B6, and CYP2E1."
    }
